ZH: 因为他欺负了我，我只能说是冤冤相报。
EN: Because he bullied me, I can only say it's a tit for tat situation.

ZH: 冤冤相报，只会让事情越发恶化。
EN: Retaliating against each other will only make things worse.

ZH: 冤冤相报，最后只会让大家都受伤。
EN: Eye for an eye will only end up hurting everyone in the end.

ZH: 我们不能一直冤冤相报，要学会原谅和忍让。
EN: We cannot always seek revenge, we must learn to forgive and let go.

ZH: 冤冤相报只会将恶意放大。
EN: Retaliation only magnifies the animosity between parties.

ZH: 当两个人不停地冤冤相报，就没有办法解决问题了。
EN: When two people keep retaliating against each other, there is no way to resolve the issue.

ZH: 冤冤相报只会加剧矛盾。
EN: Tit-for-tat will only escalate the conflict.

ZH: 只要我们能停止冤冤相报，或许可以找到解决问题的方法。
EN: If we can stop seeking retaliation, perhaps we can find a solution to the problem.

ZH: 他们之间的冤冤相报已经持续了很久。
EN: The tit-for-tat between them has been going on for a long time.

ZH: 冤冤相报永无止境。
EN: The cycle of retaliation has no end.

ZH: 冤冤相报只会让矛盾越来越深。
EN: Retaliation will only deepen the conflict.

ZH: 停止冤冤相报是解决问题的第一步。
EN: Stopping the tit-for-tat is the first step to solving the issue.

ZH: 他们之间一直都是冤冤相报，根本解决不了问题。
EN: They have been retaliating against each other all this time, unable to solve the problem.

ZH: 冤冤相报只会让处境更加困难。
EN: Retaliation will only make the situation more difficult.

ZH: 只有停止冤冤相报，才能找到和解的方法。
EN: Only by ceasing the cycle of retaliation can we find a way to reconcile.

ZH: 成熟的人不会沉浸于冤冤相报。
EN: Mature individuals do not indulge in tit-for-tat.

ZH: 冤冤相报只会增加伤害。
EN: Retaliation will only add to the harm.

ZH: 为了打破这个冤冤相报的循环，我们需要找到一个解决问题的方法。
EN: In order to break the cycle of retaliation, we need to find a way to solve the problem.

ZH: 冤冤相报是解决问题的绊脚石。
EN: Tit-for-tat is a stumbling block to solving problems.

ZH: 只有当我们停止冤冤相报，我们才能找到和解的途径。
EN: Only when we stop seeking revenge can we find a way to reconcile.
